{"lemma":"فَوْقُ","slug":"فَوْقُ","root":"ف.#.ق","root_slug":"ف-_-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-_-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَوْق","root":"فوق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":41},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adv","prep"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34848"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adv","gloss":"above"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"above, on top of"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"more than, over","examples":[{"text":"كَانُوا فَوْقَ ٱلْعِشْرِينَ","english":"They were more than twenty"},{"text":"فَإِنْ كُنَّ نِسَاءً فَوْقَ ٱثْنَتَيْنِ فَلَهُنَّ ثُلُثَا مَا تَرَكَ"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"more important than"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Originally a case form of a defective noun فَوْق (fawq, “location that is above”); see the usage note. From the root ف و ق (f w q)."},"ipa":["/faw.qu/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34848","headword_ar":"فَوْق","root":"fwq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHot","text_ar":"تَحْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) [primarily signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"location that is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and is an adv. n. (Mgh, Msb, K) of place; (Mgh, Msb;) and a simple noun, indecl., [with dammeh for its termination, when the noun to which it should be prefixed is suppressed, and the meaning of this is intended to be understood, but not the word itself;] but when it is prefixed to another noun [which is either expressed or itself (and not merely its meaning) meant to be understood, and when the noun to which it should be prefixed is suppressed and neither this nor its meaning is meant to be understood,] it is declinable. (K. [For the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwnu A@somFA waZarofFA maboniY~N","text_ar":"يَكُونُ ا@سْمًا وَظَرْفًا مَبْنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reading of the K in the TA and CK, my MS. copy of the K (which I follow in this case) has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ykwn ZrfA wAsmA mbny~A","text_ar":"يكون ظرفا واسما مبنيّا"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN fawoqa Als~aToHi","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ فَوْقَ السَّطْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, the house-top"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEimaAmapu","text_ar":"العِمَامَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoqa Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"فَوْقَ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The turban is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TafaA fawoqa AlmaA='i","text_ar":"طَفَا فَوْقَ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It floated upon the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tfw","text_ar":"طفو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Ks has mentioned the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afawoqa tanaAmu A^amo A^asofala","text_ar":"اَفَوْقَ تَنَامُ اَمْ اَسْفَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dost thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wilt thou, sleep in the part that is above"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the house &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or in the part that is below?"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the upper part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the lower part?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] with fet-h, as suppressing the noun to which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwq","text_ar":"فوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [meant to be understood as] prefixed. (TA.) Lth says that he who uses it as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sifap","text_ar":"صِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by which (like other old writers) he means an adv. n. of place] should use the accus. case, as when one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabodu A@ll~`hi fawoqa","text_ar":"عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ فَوْقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodK","text_ar":"زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Abd-Allah is above Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but if you make it simply a noun, you use the nom. case, and say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoquhu raA^osuhu","text_ar":"فَوْقُهُ رَاْسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His superior"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part is his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for in this instance it is the head itself, and you make each to be governed in the nom. case by the other. (TA.) In the saying in the Kur [xvi. 28],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxar~a Ealayohimu A@ls~aqofu mino fawoqihimo","text_ar":"فَخَرَّ عَلَيْهِمُ ا@لسَّقْفُ مِنْ فَوْقِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the roof fell on them from above them"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the utility of the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fwqhm","text_ar":"من فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is hardly apparent,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2462},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elyhm","text_ar":"عليهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes serves in its stead: but IJ says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fwqhm","text_ar":"من فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"may here have a useful office; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in relation to deeds [or events] that are difficult, and deemed onerous; [for instance,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado sironaA Ea$orFA","text_ar":"قَدْ سِرْنَا عَشْرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabaqiyato EalayonaA layolataAni","text_ar":"وَبَقِيَتْ عَلَيْنَا لَيْلَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have journeyed ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"nights"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the journeys"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two nights have remained"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though incumbent"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; &c.; so that if it were said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fxr~ Elyhm Alsqf","text_ar":"فخرّ عليهم السقف"},{"kind":"text","text":"without the adding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fwqhm","text_ar":"من فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":", it might be supposed to be like the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohimo daAruhumo qado xaribato","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمْ دَارُهُمْ قَدْ خَرِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their abode had become in a state of ruin"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a punishment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but when He [referring to God] says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwqhm","text_ar":"فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":", that meaning which was supposable ceases to be so; and the meaning becomes this, that it [the roof] fell when they were beneath it. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*o jaAw^uwkumo mino fawoqikumo wamino A^asofala minokumo","text_ar":"اـِذْ جَاوُوكُمْ مِنْ فَوْقِكُمْ وَمِنْ اَسْفَلَ مِنْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When they came to you from above you and from below you"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in the Kur [xxxiii. 10], relates to Benoo- Kureydhah, who came to them from above them; and to Kureysh and Ghatafán, who came from the district of Mekkeh, from below them. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iyna A@t~aquwA fawoqahumo yawoma A@loqiyaAmapi","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِينَ ا@تَّقُوا فَوْقَهُمْ يَوْمَ ا@لْقِيَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [ii. 208], means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But those who have been careful of their religious duties"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be above them in station"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the day of resurrection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) And one says, [agreeably with what has been stated in the first sentence of this paragraph,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu mino fawoqu","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ مِنْ فَوْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu mino fawoqK","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ مِنْ فَوْقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overpowered him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAhu mn","text_ar":"اَتَاهُ من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwq","text_ar":"فوق"},{"kind":"text","text":", as expl. in the Ham p. 128. i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaharahu","text_ar":"قَهَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, his adversary; and so a hawk, his pr? or quarry. (M and K in an expl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adal~a Ealayoh","text_ar":"اَدَلَّ عَلَيْه"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dl","text_ar":"دل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And [in a similar manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoq","text_ar":"فَوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is metaphorically used as denoting excess, (Mgh, Msb.) and excellence: (Msb:) thus one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$arapu fawoqa","text_ar":"العَشَرَةُ فَوْقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~isoEapi","text_ar":"التِّسْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ten is above nine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten exceeds nine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA fawoqa","text_ar":"هٰذَا فَوْقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superior to, that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is more excellent than that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and hence, (Mgh, Msb,) in the Kur iii. 24], (S, O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEuwDapF famaA fawoqahaA","text_ar":"بَعُوضَةً فَمَا فَوْقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gnat and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what exceeds it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in smallness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in largeness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is smaller than it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is larger than it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the latter being meant the fly [mentioned in the Kur xxii. 72] and the spider [mentioned in xxix. 40], (Fr, S, O,) and the phrase as expl. in the former sense being like the reply to him who says “ Such a one is small ”"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika wafawoqa","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ وَفَوْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And smaller than that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, O:) hence also, in the Kur iii. 12],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_ino kun~a nisaA='F fawoqa A@vonatayoni","text_ar":"فَاـِنْ كُنَّ نِسَا=ءً فَوْقَ ا@ثْنَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if they are women,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","S","O","AO","Fr"]}]}}